@node MAIN "configfile.html"
     The Preferences program     The configuration file format  

The configuration file is a plain ASCII file which can be loaded into any text editor. Its basic format is as follows:       
    	
    Each line consists of one command, optionally followed by         some parameters.     
    	
    Blank lines and lines beginning with a #         are ignored.   

Each command can have on of the following types:       
    	
    Integer (0, 1, 2, etc.). Hexadecimal numbers can be         supplied by prefixing with 0x e.g. 0x0005.     
    	
    String. Strings must be placed within quotes e.g.         &quot;taglines.txt&quot;.     
    	
    Boolean. Can be &quot;yes&quot;, &quot;no&quot;,         &quot;on&quot;, &quot;off&quot;, &quot;true&quot;,         &quot;false&quot;, &quot;0&quot; or &quot;1&quot; (quotes         optional).   

The commands can be split into the following categories:       
    	
    Enable/disable parts     
    	
    Filenames for parts     
    	
    Macros     
    	
    Miscellaneous options     
    	
    Internal options   

The commands are:       
         Enable/disable parts                   
         MOOD (boolean)         	Enable adding of MOOD kludges          
         HEADER (boolean)         	Enable adding of headers          
         NP (boolean)         	Enable adding of Now Playing lines          
         SIG (boolean)         	Enable adding of signatures          
         TAGLINE (boolean)         	Enable adding of taglines          
         Filenames                   
         MOODFILE (string)         	The file containing MOOD kludges          
         HEADERFILE (string)         	The file containing headers          
         NPFILE (string)         	The file containing Now Playing lines          
         SIGFILE (string)         	The file containing signatures          
         TAGFILE (string)         	The file containing taglines          
         Macros                   
         MACRO_N (string)         	Specifies the character sequence that is replaced by         the recipient's name          
         MACRO_FN (string)         	Specifies the character sequence that is replaced by         the recipient's first name          
         MACRO_LN (string)         	Specifies the character sequence that is replaced by         the recipient's last name          
         MACRO_D (string)         	Specifies the character sequence that is replaced by         the current date          
         MACRO_T (string)         	Specifies the character sequence that is replaced by         the current time          
         Miscellaneous settings                   
         EDITOR (string)         	The name of the text editor. In this string, @F is         replaced by the name of the OLR drop file, and @A is         replaced by any additional arguments supplied to         Tag-o-Miga          
         GUI (boolean)         	Enables or disables the use of the GUI. If this is         disabled, Tag-o-Miga will randomly select taglines for         you. Some platforms do not support the use of a GUI; in         those cases this option will be ignored.          
         NOINFO (boolean)         	If this option is enabled, Tag-o-Miga will not add         the info line to the end of your messages          
         NOREQ (boolean)         	If this option is enabled, Tag-o-Miga will not stop         and display requesters (dialog boxes in Windows-speke).         All requesters are written to the log file and silently         cancelled. This is useful if Tag-o-Miga is being run on a         BBS.          
         LOGFILE (string)         	If NOREQ is enabled, requester information is written         to this file          
         NOTAGNAME (boolean)         	If this option is enabled, Tag-o-Miga will not place         &quot;## taglines in tagfilename&quot; on the info line          
         DEFTAGFILETYPE (integer)         	Specifies the default tagfile type for tagfiles         without an [OPT] line. Acceptable values are:          
         MAKEINDEX (boolean)         	Specifies if Tag-o-Miga should build index files to         speed up tagfile scanning. It is recommended that this         option is switched on if you use the GUI or have large         tagfiles. Index files are not available under DOS due to         filename limitations.          
         BUFFER (boolean)         	This option is now deprecated.  Buffering will be 	activated automatically if required and enough memory is 	available.          
         Internal options                   
         NETWORK2 (boolean)         	This option should be kept switched OFF. It remains         only for compatibility reasons.          
         USECOUNT (integer)         	This option should not be altered. It keeps track of         the number of times the program has been run, so a         Postcardware reminder can be displayed after prolonged         use.        
	----------------------------------------
  

